The paper proposes a visual odometry system for a camera rig, which involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The system also uses machine learning (cs.LG) algorithms for improved feature matching and pose estimation. Additionally, the system involves online calibration and correction of camera poses, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
